<p>The first limitation I see in my implementation is the width, which in this example looks clearly huge and is not necessary, so I need to make the width an optional parameter.</p>
<p>We moved on from this <em>shortcode</em> that did not allow to set the width (it was predefined as 100% in the styles):</p>
<pre tabindex="0"><code>{{$svg := .Get 0}}
&lt;div class=&#34;svg-fill-background&#34;&gt;
    {{ $svg | readFile | safeHTML }}
&lt;/div&gt;
</code></pre><p>To the next one, where we can optionally indicate the percentage width, and the change can be seen below (we could extend this to more properties, but it&rsquo;s not necessary for now):</p>
<pre tabindex="0"><code>{{$svg := .Get 0}}
{{$width := .Get 1 | default &#34;100%&#34;}}

&lt;div class=&#34;svg-fill-background&#34; style=&#34;width: {{$width}}; margin: 0 auto&#34;&gt;
    {{ $svg | readFile | safeHTML }}
&lt;/div&gt;
</code></pre><pre tabindex="0"><code>{{&lt; svg &#34;static/images/blog/004/example.svg&#34; &#34;40%&#34;&gt;}}
</code></pre>


